se.inera.axel.shs.broker.messagestore

Interface MessageLogService


  • public interface MessageLogService
    The broker's interface to the message database log/queue.

    This log is used to store the incoming message (with saveMessage(se.inera.axel.shs.mime.ShsMessage) and get a reference to an ShsMessageEntry-object. (Claim-Check-pattern).
    That object is then processed and dispatched inside the broker until the message is to be sent to a remote destination or handed to a client. Then the original message is fetched from the database with loadMessage(ShsMessageEntry).
    An implementation of this interface would typically interact with MessageStoreService to handle the actual store/fetch of the real ShsMessage.

    • Method Detail

      • saveMessage

        ShsMessageEntry saveMessage(se.inera.axel.shs.mime.ShsMessage message)
        Saves a message to the physical message store and returns a log entry containing header values and routing status of the message. A txId only be used once (in one transaction), use the other methods to make updates to the entry.
        Parameters:
        message - The message as it enters the server.
        Returns:
        A log entry that should be used during message routing.
        Throws:
        MessageAlreadyExistsException - if the same txId is reused in another transaction.

      • deleteMessage

        void deleteMessage(ShsMessageEntry messageEntry)
        Deletes a message from the physical message store and returns a log entry containing header values and routing status of the message. A txId only be used once (in one transaction), use the other methods to make updates to the entry.
        Parameters:
        message - The message as it enters the server.
        Throws:
        MessageNotFoundException - if the txId does not have a message

      • loadEntry

        ShsMessageEntry loadEntry(String shsTo,
                        String txId)
        Loads a log entry from the transaction database given an shs address and transaction id of the message.
        Parameters:
        shsTo - An shs address, usually an org. nbr.
        txId - Transaction id in the format of an uuid
        Returns:
        The log entry, if found.
        Throws:
        MessageNotFoundException - if the message cannot be found.
